<p>The couple's son Miles, two, looked adorable as he enjoyed the front seat of the cart in a grey long-sleeve tee and denim shorts. </p>

<p>Both Miles and Luna were protected during their outing in their own reusable face masks amid the coronavirus pandemic.  </p>

<p>John got busy unloading groceries into the car ahead of the dinner Chrissy prepared for friend Jen Atkin and Mike Rosenthal. </p>

<p>Earlier in the day, the model, 34, shared an adorable scavenger hunt they put on for Luna. </p>

<p>Roses: Luna, four, was spotted holding a large bouquet of pink roses likely for her model mom who was at home and is currently expecting the couple's third child, while Miles sat in the front seat of the basket  </p>

<p>After playtime: Chrissy documented the hunt on her Instagram Stories, sharing the clues that John read aloud to help her on her journey </p>

<p>Chrissy documented the hunt on her Instagram Stories, sharing the clues that John read aloud to help her on her journey. </p>

<p>Clues for Luna included 'Dada + Cat were the first words you said, your very first clue is on the book on your bed.' </p>

<p>As well as 'My brilliant little moon...You're so happy and free! Run your monkey toes to the place Miles goes pee!'</p>

<p>The final clue, 'Your last clue is here! I hope you fun. Meet mom in her room to see what you've won' led Luna to her parent's bedroom where Chrissy laid out gold coins for the four-year-old to collect. </p>

